                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-07T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 7, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Referring to my telegram 77, July 6, 10 p.m.,<note n="79" xml:id="d597fn79"
                        >Not printed.</note> Under Secretary for Foreign Affairs told me today that
                    Bolivia has accepted in principle the Argentine suggestion for bringing about
                    immediate renewal of diplomatic relations between that country and Paraguay. He
                    expressed hope that the Argentine good offices would succeed but considered the
                    situation uncertain. He supposed that a decision for or against would be reached
                    within the next 3 days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
